 on an exhale.";i:2;s:82:"Alternately use an exhale to fold forward into Uttanasana for a more passive exit.";i:3;s:163:"About Press Copyright Contact us Creators Advertise Developers Terms Privacy Policy Safety How YouTube works Test new features Press Copyright Contact us Creators.";i:4;s:95:"Chair pose is a standing squat that let upper and lower body muscles strengthen simultaneously.";i:5;s:96:"While holding this pose for a while you will feel an intense stretch in the shoulder upper back.";i:6;s:73:"On regular practice your quadriceps gluteus calves ankles get strengthen.";i:7;s:117:"This pose is also called the Chair pose just because the posture resembles like one is sitting on an invisible chair.";i:8;s:66:"This pose is one of the first pose in the Sun Salutation B series.";i:9;s:146:"It needs ample strength with the quadricep muscles to help your hips get the right support and give the knees a comfort to hold the pose for long.";i:10;s:130:"Working on the alignment of the hips along with the knees and the pelvic region is very essential to get comfortable in this pose.";i:11;s:37:"Hold this pose for 5-10 slow breaths.";i:12;s:92:"Inhale and press through your feet to extend your legs and return to Tadasana Mountain pose.";i:13;s:43:"Exhale and release your arms to your sides.";i:14;s:74:"Rise to standing on an inhale and sink back into the posture on an exhale.";i:15;s:40:"Keep your arms extended in front of you.";i:16;s:107:"Sometimes known as fierce or powerful pose Chair pose is part of the yogis beloved Salutation to the Sun B.";i:17;s:64:"Chair pose is a relatively easy pose to learn for all abilities.";i:18;s:96:"Some of the best thigh and quadriceps strengthening and training can come from long chair holds.";i:19;s:71:"Chair Pose will strengthen your thighs helping to stabilize your knees.";i:20;s:107:"Your ankles will become more limber and sturdy and your arms and shoulders will gain power and flexibility.";i:21;s:107:"As you reach your arms up and stretch the muscles between your ribs youll increase your breathing capacity.";i:22;s:134:"The anatomy of chair pose utkatasana BKS Iyengar introduced the world to the idea of using props to change the anatomy of a yoga pose.";i:23;s:115:"He had a deep understanding of which muscles tendons bones and vital organs were involved in every asana he taught.";i:24;s:45:"Exhale bend your knees and sit back in Chair.";i:25;s:49:"Engage your lower abs to support your lower back.";i:26;s:72:"Shift your weight back into the centre of your heels and drop your hips.";i:27;s:80:"Check that both knees point straight ahead and that you can still see your toes.";i:28;s:59:"Hold the pose for 3-5 breaths in and out through your nose.";i:29;s:127:"A good way to make the chair Pose more comfortable is by pressing the heads of your thigh bones in the direction of your heels.";i:30;s:59:"When in the pose take the hands to the tops of your thighs.";i:31;s:138:"Place your palms where the groin folds over and press the thighs downwards towards the heels while also pressing the heels into the floor.";i:32;s:44:"It will help you to hold the posture longer.";i:33;s:100:"It is a good idea to do the Chair Pose after you have finished all the other standing yoga postures.";i:34;s:82:"You can then start with the sitting yoga postures or the lying down yoga postures.";i:35;s:34:"Benefits of Utkatasana Chair Pose.";i:36;s:43:"Exercises the spine hips and chest muscles.";i:37;s:36:"Helps strengthen the lower back and.";i:38;s:20:"Chair Pose Benefits.";i:39;s:73:"This pose is excellent for strengthening many muscles in your lower body.";i:40;s:51:"It engages your calves hamstrings quads and glutes.";i:41;s:66:"It also helps to strengthen your core and challenges your balance.";i:42;s:131:"Chair Pose balances the bottom three chakras the Root Chakra Muladhara Sacral Chakra Svadhisthana and Solar Plexus Chakra Manipura.";i:43;s:124:"This posture helps ground and root the practitioner into the present moment and physical body while also allowing himher to.";i:44;s:89:"Chair Pose is a standing yoga posture that tones the entire body particularly the thighs.";i:45;s:83:"It involves sitting back as if youre about to fall seated into a chair but holding.";i:46;s:33:"Breathe and hold for 3-6 breaths.";i:47;s:101:"Inhale and press down into the feet straightening the legs and inhale the arms up toward the ceiling.";i:48;s:29:"Exhale release the arms down.";i:49;s:79:"Chair pose strongly strengthens the lower body while stretching the upper back.";i:50;s:54:"This posture invigorates and energizes the whole body.";i:51;s:165:"Utkatasana is a standing posture that on the outside appears simple enough but looks can be deceiving this pose will challenge beginners and advanced students alike.";i:52;s:140:"As with the previous mountain and tree poses the primary focus is placed on the legs and pelvis to stabilise and ground the asana and there.";i:53;s:53:"Chair Pose or Utkatasana is often called fierce pose.";i:54;s:113:"This comes as no surprise to yogis who regularly practice this relatively basic but nonetheless challenging pose.";i:55;s:128:"Holding this pose for an extended period of time or multiple times in a sequence calls for a fierceness of mind as well as body.";i:56;s:47:"LEARN How to do Utkatasana Chair Pose properly.";i:57;s:106:"Know the benefits and contraindications from Indian Yogi SandeepFor information about our Yoga Courses vi.";i:58;s:136:"Hold your lower body facing towards the right leg as you lift your arms up to the ceiling while inhaling arriving at the warrior 1 pose.";i:59;s:29:"Hold on to for three breaths.";i:60;s:36:"Chair Warrior II- Virabhadrasana II.";i:61;s:89:"This asana is also a beginners level yoga pose that helps strengthen the ankles and legs.";i:62;s:80:"The Chair warrior 2 pose stretches shoulders legs groin lungs thorax and ankles.";i:63;s:24:"Begin with exhaling and.";i:64;s:87:"Chair Pose is so important for everyday strength of getting up and down out of a chair.";i:65;s:94:"At work you should do about 30 repetitions of this sit to stand stand to sit motion every day.";i:66;s:78:"Add a couple of long holds just at the point before you let yourself sit down.";i:67;s:31:"Make sure you breathe and hold.";i:68;s:73:"Hold pose Hold the pose for 30 seconds to a minute or as long as you can.";i:69;s:100:"Release pose Release the pose on an inhale by slowly straightening your legs and lowering your arms.";i:70;s:76:"Now the next time somebody tells you to pull up a chair you know what to do.";}}